tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE employees ( 
    employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY, 
    employee_name VARCHAR(50), 
    access_level INT, 
    assigned_tasks TEXT[], 
    completed_maintenance_work BOOLEAN 
);

CREATE TABLE employees (
  employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  employee_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  access_level INT NOT NULL,
  supervisor_id INT,
  created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE tasks (
  task_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  task_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  assigned_to INT,
  created_at TIMESTAMP,
  completed BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE maintenance_work (
  work_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  task_id INT,
  employee_id INT,
  start_date DATE,
  end_date DATE,
  status VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE maintenance_work (
    work_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    task_id INT,
    employee_id INT,
    completion_date DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (task_id) REFERENCES tasks(task_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (employee_id) REFERENCES employees(employee_id)
);

CREATE TABLE work_log (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    work_id INT,
    log_description TEXT,
    log_date TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (work_id) REFERENCES maintenance_work(work_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Tasks (
    task_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    task_name VARCHAR(255),
    deadline DATE,
    assigned_to INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (assigned_to) REFERENCES Employees(employee_id) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

CREATE TABLE MaintenanceWork (
    maintenance_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    task_id INT,
    completion_date DATE,
    status VARCHAR(20),
    FOREIGN KEY (task_id) REFERENCES Tasks(task_id) ON DELETE CASCADE
);
